# GPIB MCP — Cursor install (#90)

Cursor runs local **stdio** MCP servers, so this uses the same `GpibMcp.exe` directly.

## 1. Get the server
Download `__ZIP__` from the GitHub Release and unzip it to:

```
%LOCALAPPDATA%\Programs\GpibMcp
```

(so the server is at `__EXE__`). NI-VISA / NI-488.2 must be installed on the machine.

## 2a. One-click — "Add to Cursor"
Open this deeplink (or use the **Add to Cursor** badge that encodes it):

```
__CURSOR_DEEPLINK__
```

## 2b. Manual config
Add to `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (global) or `.cursor/mcp.json` (project):

```json
__CONFIG__
```

## 3. Use it
Cursor → **Settings → Tools & MCP** — confirm `gpib` is listed and enabled, then ask Cursor to drive your
instruments.
